@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

@{b}IfNoDrive@{ub} is a small program which returns a warning
code (or, optionally, reboots) if it cannot find a drive that
you specify as a part of your system.

@{b}IfNoDrive@{ub} comes with source in @{b}AmigaE@{ub}, so you
can change it if you want.

@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"

Template:

    DEVICE/A,R=REBOOT/S,D=DELAY/N

Usage:

    Early in your startup sequence, put a line like

        C:IfNoDrive HD1 REBOOT DELAY=3

    (assuming that you need to check whether the drive with the
    partition HD1: has spun up to speed yet).

    @{b}IfNoDrive@{ub}'s default behaviour is to return a value;
    the values of these return codes are as follows:

        0  - Success.
        5  - Specified drive not present.
        10 - Could not lock device list.
        20 - Bad arguments (will also print out an error
             message).

    With the @{b}REBOOT@{ub} switch, if the drive is not present, the
    program will reset the computer, to give the drive time to spin
    up.

    The @{b}DELAY@{ub} parameter is the time (in seconds) that the
    program will delay before it reboots. It is only effective when
    used with the @{b}REBOOT@{ub} switch. The program automatically
    limits the delay time to between 0 and 20 seconds. (The default
    behaviour of the program is to not delay the reboot at all.)

    Do *NOT* add the colon (:) at the end of the device/drive name.
    @{b}IfNoDrive@{ub} does not do any processing of the input, it
    just uses it directly.

@endnode

@node HISTORY "History"

    @{FG shine}v0.1 (15.3.97)@{FG text}         1204 bytes       (@{b}Unreleased@{ub})

    *   Initial version.


    @{FG shine}v0.2 (17.3.97)@{FG text}         1300 bytes       @{b}First Aminet release@{ub}

    *   Made the return of a warning code the default behaviour.
    *   Added the REBOOT switch.


    @{FG shine}v0.3 (23.3.97)@{FG text}         1412 bytes       @{b}Second Aminet release@{ub}

    *   Added the DELAY switch.


    @{FG shine}v0.4 (6.8.97)@{FG text}          1336 bytes       @{b}Third Aminet release@{ub}

    *   Fixed a possible (but very unlikely) bug in the
        reading of the DELAY parameter.
    *   Bumped the maximum DELAY time to 20 seconds, changed
        default time before reboot to 0.
    *   'Optimized' the source code to remove some pointless
        initializations, etc.


    @{FG shine}v0.5 (28.8.97)@{FG text}         1228 bytes       @{b}Fourth Aminet release@{ub}

    *   More optimizations.


    @{FG shine}v0.6 (2.10.97)@{FG text}         1196 bytes       @{b}Fifth Aminet release@{ub}

    *   Even more optimizations. ;p The program is now
        actually smaller than v0.1, but offers more
        features.


    @{FG shine}v0.7 (8.2.98)@{FG text}          1168 bytes       @{b}Sixth Aminet release@{ub}

    *   Added a new return code if the program could not lock the
        device list.
    *   Optimizations. Yes, the program is even smaller!


@endnode

